&gt; love wrote:
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; I tried doing this, but it executed only the last
&gt; one.:myruntests
&gt; &gt; [1]); 4 times::
&gt; &gt; Why is it so???
&gt; 
&gt; Each test is a different object, but you added the
&gt; same object (test) 
&gt; three times. Only the last test executes because you
&gt; did this:
&gt; 
&gt; create test
&gt; change its name to A, then add it to the list
&gt; change its name to B, then add it to the list again
&gt; change its name to C, then add it to the list a
&gt; third time
&gt; 
&gt; At the end, you have /the same test/ in the list
&gt; three times, and 
&gt; they&#39;re all named C (in your case, &quot;test1&quot;).
&gt; 
&gt; So each test has to be a separate object.
&gt; 
&gt; suite.addTest(createMyTest(&quot;test7&quot;));
&gt; suite.addTest(createMyTest(&quot;test3&quot;));
&gt; suite.addTest(createMyTest(&quot;test1&quot;));
&gt; 
&gt; public Test createMyTest(String name) {
&gt;      MyTest test = new MyTest();
&gt;      test.setName(name);
&gt;      return test;
&gt; }
&gt; 
&gt; Or add this constructor to MyTest:
&gt; 
&gt; public MyTest(String name) {
&gt;      setName(name);
&gt; }
&gt; 
&gt; Now:
&gt; 
&gt; suite.addTest(new MyTest(&quot;test7&quot;));
&gt; ...
&gt; 
&gt; Either way, the three tests are different objects,
&gt; so they can execute 
&gt; different test methods.
&gt; 
&gt; I hope this helps.
